<subSubSection pageNumber="686" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="686">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="686">Note:</emphasis>
Although Wade (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="686">J. Bot.</emphasis>
80: 128. 1944) indicated Clifford material (BM), identifiable with 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Hill" authorityName="Hill" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Myosotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="686">M. palustris</emphasis>
(L.) Hill
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, there have been difficulties with the application of the name, which has been used in the sense of both 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Hill" authorityName="Hill" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Mentha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="686">M. arvensis</emphasis>
(L.) Hill
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Myosotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="686">M. palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and occasionally discarded as a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="686">nomen ambiguum.</emphasis>
Verberne (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="686">Acta Bot. Neerl.</emphasis>
8: 330-337. 1959) and Holub (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="686">Preslia</emphasis>
38: 130-136. 1966) have both discussed the matter at length. It may be that a formal proposal (for conservation or rejection) will be needed to resolve this problem.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
